Fourier Series &amp; Wave Equation, Using Partial Sums</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Author" style="Author"><Font family="Times New Roman">by David Canright, Math. Dept.,  Code MA/Ca, Naval Postgraduate School, Monterey, CA,<Font encoding="ISO8859-1">
dcanright@nps.navy.mil, \251 2000 David Canright.</Font></Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">Note:  This worksheet allows exploration &amp; plotting of Fourier Series (using partial sums </Font><Equation input-equation="S[N]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJTRzYjJSJORw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman">) in an educational setting.</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"/><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="_cstyle257"><Font bold="true" family="Times New Roman">Introduction: Setting up the Worksheet</Font></Text-field></Title></Section><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">restart;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Normal"><Font style="Maple Input">with(plots):  </Font><Font family="Times New Roman">need "plots" package for animation below</Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="_cstyle258"><Font bold="true" family="Times New Roman">Section I: General Definitions for Fourier Series</Font></Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">Note: <Font style="emphasis">do this section only once</Font> (before L, a0, etc. are ever defined)</Font></Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">  term: one term (#n) in series
  SN:  partial sum (up to N) of series</Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">term := an*cos(n*Pi*x/L) + bn*sin(n*Pi*x/L);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">SN := a0/2 + 'sum( an*cos(n*Pi*x/L) + bn*sin(n*Pi*x/L), n=1..N )';</Text-field></Input></Group></Section><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="_cstyle259"><Font bold="true" family="Times New Roman">Section II: Define Particular Fourier Series</Font></Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">come back and <Font style="emphasis">redo this section for each different Fourier Series</Font></Font></Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group><Text-field layout="Heading 2" style="Heading 2"><Font family="Times New Roman">You have <Font size="14" style="emphasis">two choices</Font>:</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">   If you <Font style="emphasis">know</Font> the function <Font style="emphasis">f</Font>, use the <Font style="emphasis">first subsection</Font></Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">   If you <Font style="emphasis">know</Font> the <Font style="emphasis">coefficients</Font>, use the <Font style="emphasis">second subsection</Font></Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">   If you know f and the coeffiecients, use either subsection</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">but <Font style="emphasis">do not do both</Font>!</Font></Text-field><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 2" style="Heading 2"><Font family="Times New Roman">Section IIa: Either Calculate Coefficients by Integrals</Font></Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">If you know the function f and choose L, </Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">you can calculate the coefficients:  </Font><Equation input-equation="a[0]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJhRzYjIiIh</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman">  </Font><Equation input-equation="a[n]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJhRzYjJSJuRw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman">  </Font><Equation input-equation="b[n]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJiRzYjJSJuRw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman">  </Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">using the integral formulas</Font></Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">define</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> particular function <Font style="emphasis">f</Font>  
(default example is for f(x)= {0 for -1&lt;x&lt;0 and x for 0&lt;x&lt;1})<Font style="emphasis">
modify this definition for other series</Font></Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">f := piecewise(x&gt;0,x);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="emphasis"><Font family="Times New Roman">choose L</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">L := 2;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">Now evaluate the integrals to find the coefficients</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">Note: these steps must be done <Font style="emphasis">in order</Font></Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">Int( f, x=-L..L ) / L ;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">value(%);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">a0 := %;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">Int( f*cos(n*Pi*x/L), x=-L..L ) / L ;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">value(%);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">simplify(%,trig,assume=integer);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">an := %;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">Int( f*sin(n*Pi*x/L), x=-L..L ) / L ;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">value(%);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">simplify(%,trig,assume=integer);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">bn := %;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">At this point, have defined the series, so <Font style="emphasis">skip down to</Font> the <Font style="emphasis">plots</Font></Font></Text-field></Input></Group></Section><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 2" style="Heading 2"><Font family="Times New Roman">Section 2b:  or Specify Coefficients:  </Font><Equation input-equation="a[n]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJhRzYjJSJuRw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman">  </Font><Equation input-equation="b[n]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJiRzYjJSJuRw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman">  &amp; L</Font></Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">come back and <Font style="emphasis">redo this section for each different Fourier Series</Font></Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">You must first know the formula for each coefficient</Font></Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">define particular series coefficients and L
(default example is from text pg. 24: </Font><Equation input-equation="Sum(cos(n*x)/(n^2),n = 1 .. infinity);" style="2D Comment">NiMtJSRTdW1HNiQqJi0lJGNvc0c2IyomJSJuRyIiIiUieEdGLEYsKiRGKyIiIyEiIi9GKztGLCUpaW5maW5pdHlH</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman"> )<Font style="emphasis">
modify these definitions to plot other series</Font></Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">L := Pi;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">a0 := 0;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">an :=  1/n^2;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">bn :=  0;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">define</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> particular function <Font style="emphasis">f</Font>  (sum of series)
(default example: we don't know f, so set to 0 )<Font style="emphasis">
modify this definition for other series</Font></Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">Note: if do not know f, set f := 0;</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">f := 0;</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input"/></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">At this point, have defined the series, so <Font style="emphasis">go on to</Font> the <Font style="emphasis">plots</Font></Font></Text-field></Input></Group></Section></Section><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1"><Font family="Times New Roman">Section III: Plot Partial Sum </Font><Equation input-equation="S[N]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJTRzYjJSJORw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman"> and/or Terms of Series</Font></Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="emphasis"><Font family="Times New Roman">try changing N on any or all of these</Font></Text-field><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">choose N</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> to plot the partial sum </Font><Equation input-equation="S[N]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJTRzYjJSJORw==</Equation></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">N := 3;
plot( SN, x=-L .. L);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">choose N</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> to plot term #N</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">N := 3;
plot( subs(n=N,term), x=-L .. L);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">choose N</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> to plot a partial sum and all the terms up to N</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">N := 3;
plot( { a0/2, seq(subs(n=i,term),i=1..N), SN }, x=-L .. L);</Text-field></Input></Group></Section><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1"><Font family="Times New Roman">Section IV:  Examine Convergence of Fourier Series</Font></Text-field></Title><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Normal"><Font style="Maple Input">plot( f, x=-L..L );</Font><Font family="Times New Roman">  look at function over one period</Font></Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">choose N</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> to compare the function f to the partial sum </Font><Equation input-equation="S[N]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJTRzYjJSJORw==</Equation></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">N := 5;
plot( [SN,f], x=-L .. L);</Text-field></Input></Group><Group><Input><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman" style="emphasis">choose max N</Font><Font family="Times New Roman"> to animate the convergence of the partial sum </Font><Equation input-equation="S[N]" style="2D Comment">NiMmJSJTRzYjJSJORw==</Equation><Font family="Times New Roman"> to f</Font></Text-field><Text-field layout="Normal" prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input">Nmax := 5;
display([seq(plot( [SN,f], x=-L .. L),N=0..Nmax)], insequence=true);</Text-field></Input></Group></Section><Section><Title><Text-field layout="Heading 1" style="Heading 1"><Font family="Times New Roman">Conclusion:<Font style="_cstyle261"> This worksheet clearly demonstrates Maple's ability to be used as an Educational tool for advanced mathematical concepts.</Font></Font></Text-field></Title><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"/><Text-field layout="Normal" style="Normal"><Font family="Times New Roman">Disclaimer:  While every effort has been made to validate the solutions in this worksheet, Waterloo Maple Inc. and the contributors are not responsible for any errors contained and are not liable for any damages resulting from the use of this material.</Font></Text-field></Section><Text-field/></Worksheet>